subject: p18828251
History: Cough and fever, to assess for pneumonia.
Findings: In comparison with the study of, there is little overall change. Continued enlargement of the cardiac silhouette in a patient with intact midline sternal wires after CABG. No evidence of vascular congestion. The overall discordancy raises possibility of cardiomyopathy. Calcification is again seen in coronary vessels. No evidence of acute focal pneumonia.
